Not all wage freezes in the world will prevent the European petrochemical industry from being penalized by a cheap U.S. shale gas.
As a result, the revolt roars, especially in France, one of the great leaders of the EU.
After the war, the French political elite saw the EU as a means of controlling Germany and putting Paris on an equal footing with Washington.
